==English==
===Etymology===
STEN is an acronym, deriving from the names of the weapon's chief designers, Major Reginald '''S'''heperd and Harold '''T'''urpin, and '''EN'''field, the location of the Royal Small Arms Factory (RSAF) at Enfield Lock in London. 

